node.text:
Wrist pain? This video is long overdue. Do you experience wrist pain when exercising? [save it, share it, and read below]

Here ar some tips on stretches and exercises you can do to not strain your wrists while exercising.

Tip 1: keep your resists flexible in all planes of motion. Without an adequate range of motion in our wrist we end up compressing into a joint that isn’t ready to take on that pressure passively or actively. 

How many reps/weight? Well, listen to your body and be gentle. The more you perform these and be progressive with the work (as in- every day before a workout) the less you have to worry about reps, and focus on how you feel. Take 5 mins and make these a habit.

1️⃣ Warm up flexibility work: 

1:Extended arms wrist flexión and extension.
2:Extended arms wrist rotations.
3:All 4’s rotation/flexion/extension variations.

2️⃣ Strong wrists are more stable during weight-bearing exercises. Strengthening your wrists and forearms (as the forearms control the wrists) is also key not only to be able to hold heavier weight more securely, but to bear the load of your own body weight or push/pull weight. 

1: Farmers walks (walk 50-100 feet. Use progressive weight). These are great to add to your workout prescriptions. 
2: Dumbbell  flexión and extension.
3: Dumbell  pronation and supination.

If you are injured, recovering from injury, and or are experiencing extreme inflammation and pain consult a PT. These tips are for healthy individuals who don’t require medical help. 

Let me know how these do for you. 

Join my tribe pointing down 👇🏽 

www.massyarias.com
#mawarriors #childofGod

¿Dolor de muñeca? ¿Sientes dolor de muñeca al hacer ejercicio? [guárdalo, compártelo y lee a continuación] 

Aquí hay algunos consejos sobre estiramientos y ejercicios que puedes hacer para no tensar las muñecas mientras haces ejercicio. 

Consejo 1: menten tus muñecas flexibles en todos los planos de movimiento. Sin un rango de movimiento adecuado en nuestra muñeca, terminamos comprimiéndonos en una articulación que no está lista para asumir esa presión de forma pasiva o activa. 

Continuación en los comentarios.

node.title: WRIST PAIN WHILE WORKING OUT? DOLOR DE MUÑECAS AL ENTRENAR?

node.text:
Food is fuel and it is also medicine. Hopefully today I teach you a few nutrition 101 tips. 

This breakfast has been staple in my diet for many years to maintain a healthy body composition, digestive system, increased energy levels, and fuel for my strength workouts. 

Food isn’t the enemy. Try this recipe out and let me know how you like it. 

Ps: I really enjoy organic content. I had fun doing this live!

node.title: My impromptu breakfast this week [the best oatmeal ever]

“It isn’t about being good at something. It’s about being good to yourself!”. 

Mastering the mind and getting in tune with this body. Truly enjoying this process of exploration and discovery while finishing the last week of volume 2 of my Elevate program before we launch it. I’m so excited for everyone who will be joining.

Mentally and physically  the strongest I’ve ever been and I cannot wait to help you unlock the same feelings. 

Happy Tuesday tribe. Try it out #MAELEVATE volume 1 👇🏽 

www.MassyArias.com
_____________________________________

Domina tu mente y tu cuerpo te seguirá;  no se trata de ser buenos en cualquier práctica, pero de ser buenos con nosotros mismos.

Como usas tu cuerpo y tu mente? El ejercicio y el movimiento son herramientas de salud, y bienestar mental. 

Muévete!

node.title: Master the mind and the body will follow || Fluyendo 💫

node.text:
“I create what I want my Monday to feel like
I get to choose those thoughts
My weekend is not a retreat from my weekdays
My life, my feelings are not determined by a day of the week
My life has no day
It has moments”~ @iamtonijones 

Monday’s are meant to be crushed just like any day of the week. 

Today the goal isn’t to teach you how to crush your Monday with the perfect workout, but to teach you a mindset. Shift your gears to the word “discipline”. You’re disciplined no matter what day of the week it is. Responsibility will always knock on your door, but discipline is what will help you be consistent.

Being disciplined doesn’t require you to overthink. It requires you to plan accordingly. I didn’t know what I was going to do today with the time I had available/planned, but I chose to explore and still move for my mental health.

Everything got done, even me filming this moment for you all today!

It’s a mindset!

🎶 @masego #tadow

www.Massyarias.com 
———————————————————————————

Zero ansiedad!

“Yo creo los sentimientos que quiero sentir los Lunes.  Mi fin de semana no es un retiro de mis días de semana. Mi vida y mis sentimientos no están determinados por un día de la semana. Mi vida no tiene dias; mi vida tiene momentos " 

Los lunes están destinados a ser conquistados  como cualquier día de la semana. 

Hoy el objetivo no es enseñarte cómo conquistar tu Lunes con el entrenamiento perfecto, sino enseñarte una mentalidad. 

La "disciplina". Eres disciplinado sin importar el día de la semana. La responsabilidad siempre llamará a tu puerta, pero la disciplina es lo que te ayudará a ser consistente. Ser disciplinado no requiere que pienses demasiado. Requiere que planifiques en consecuencia. 

No sabía qué iba a hacer hoy con el tiempo que tenía disponible / planeado, pero elegí explorar y dedicar mi tiempo para mi salud mental. ¡Todo se hizo, incluso el filmar este momento para todos ustedes hoy!

node.title: #Mondaymotivation Mantra [read below] || Mangra del Lunes [lee abajo].

node.text:
An epic leg day Hamstrings Glute focused [save for later, share, and let’s crush it] #ma60day 

You’ll perform each movement of a the above supersets with little to no rest in between. Rest 1:30-2mins  between supersets. 3 sets of every superset. 

Superset 1: 

Dumbbell step ups: 6 per leg 
Single leg hip thurst:  6 per leg

Superset 2:

•Stiff leg deadlifts: 12reps 
•Physioball hamtring curls: 8reps per leg 

Superset 3:

•Forward and reverse lunges: 6 repetitions per side.
•Frog banded Hip Bridges: 12 repetitions.

🎶 @sza @kendricklamar #allthestars

Join my tribe @mawarriors community and let me help you change your lifestyle with my comprehensive programs. 👇🏽 

www.MassyArias.com
#childofGod #mawarrior
________________________________________

Un día de piernas concentración femoral y de glúteos. Esta rutina les va a encantar. Sálvala, compártela, y dale!

El entrenamiento: realizarás cada movimiento de un súper conjunto con poco descanso entre ellos. Descansa de 1:30-2mins entre cada serie del súper conjunto. 3 series por superconjunto.

Superconjunto 1:

•Step up con mancuerna: 6 reps por lado
•Hip thurst con una sola pierna : 6 reps por lado.

Superconjunto 2:

•Peso muerto: 12 reps
•Curl femoral con bola physio: 8 reps por lado

Superconjunto 3:

•Zancada delantera y reversa 6 reps por pierna.
•Puentes en posición rana con abducción de banda: 12 repeticiones.

Repeticiones controladas con enfoque en la forma y la mecánica de cada ejercicio. No te enfoques en el peso que estás usando, pero en la calidad y la conexión muscular de cada 
movimiento.

Dale!

#hijadecristo

node.text:
Today I’ll teach you how to not rely on machines, but to use your body as a machine. 

Today’s circuit : 

•Reverse to forward lunge 8 reps per side
•Single leg Plank with knee cross over 8reps per side. 
•Standing single leg retro kick back 10 reps per side.
•Rotational plank 8 reps per side 

In an advanced level of training  I didn’t take a break between the sets of this circuit as a way to challenge myself. Body weight training can still challenge your body without using heavy resistance or any equipment at all.  Your body is a machine and you can use it to train anywhere. Beginners/intermediate levels rest as needed.

I want you to follow along and share this circuit with your friends and family. This is a preview of my new upcoming program. So get ready! 

We can use machines or we can become the machines. Join my @mawarriors community and let me teach you how to reach your goals 👇🏾

🎶 @santigold 

www.Massyarias.com
#maelevate #childofGod
_____________________________________________

Hoy te enseñaré cómo no depender de las máquinas, sino cómo usar tu cuerpo como una máquina. 

Circuito de hoy: • zancada reversa y  hacia adelante 8 repeticiones por lado 
• Plancha con una sola  pierna con cruce de rodillas en 8 repeticiones por lado. 
• Kickback con banda unilateral 10 repeticiones por lado. 
• Plancha rotacional 8 repeticiones por lado 

En un nivel avanzado de entrenamiento, no me tomé un descanso entre los sets de este circuito para desafiarme. Entrenar con tu peso corporal puede desafiar a tu cuerpo sin usar resistencia con pesas o ni ningún equipo. 

Tu cuerpo es una máquina y puedes usarlo para entrenar en cualquier lugar. Los niveles principiantes / intermedios descansen según sea necesario. 

Quiero que sigas y compartas este circuito con tus amigos y familiares. 
Trátala y dime que tal. Rutina de cuerpo completo.

#hijasecristo

node.title: Do NOT understimate body weight training || No subestimes tú peso corporal!

node.text:
“You’ll have good days, bad days, overwhelming days, too tired days, I’m awesome days, I can’t go days . And everyday you’ll still show up”

Motivation is a tricky feeling that can come  and go very quickly. Initially when you have a goal you’ll find yourself highly motivated to accomplish it. Then we get into into the mundane routine of the work and soon that motivation goes away. 

So here’s one of the tools I have used to stay motivated all these years:

🚨 Pick an area of that goal you can break down making it more attainable, rather than looking at your goal as this imposible task that will take months or years to accomplish.

Getting stronger
Getting a faster mile
Getting more flexible

🚨Focus on those small wins and those milestones.

Discipline and will power need to take over in order for you not to lose your way. The discipline you have to develop can be strengthened with burst of motivation by hitting milestones. My milestone with @mawarriors community has been picking an extra activity that makes me feel my best and that is by getting stronger and becoming more flexible bringing yoga/mobility back to my regimen with #maelevate. My goal of 315 is extra curricular but it gives me the satisfaction of showing up and breaking that goal. 

What goal will you set yourself?

WATCH THE REST OF THE WORKOUT ON YOUTUBE. EVERY WEDNESDAY THERES A NEW VIDEO DROPPING.

www.Massyarias.con
________________________________________

LET ME MOTIVATE YOU TODAY. 

Motivation is a tricky feeling that can come  and go very quickly. Initially when you have a goal you’ll find yourself highly motivated to accomplish it. Then we get into into the mundane routine of the work and soon that motivation goes away. 

So here’s one of the tools I have used to stay motivated all these years:

🚨 Pick an area of that goal you can break down making it more attainable, rather than looking at your goal as this imposible task that will take months or years to accomplish.

Getting stronger
Getting a faster mile
Getting more flexible

node.text:
It’s counterintuitive to think that when you’re sore after a workout, movement is what you need to feel better. 

When your body moves it increases blood flow sending rich oxygenated blood to those sore muscles. This helps speed recovery reducing soreness. 

With this flow we are moving and stretching our entire body. 

So try this mobility/stretching flow on days you’re recovering from hard workouts. Start light and don’t force the movements. Be gentle with each stretch. When doing this flow hold each stretch for 10 deep breaths doing three rounds of each transition.

1:Arms overhead to forward fold
2: Highplank
3: Warrior 1
4: Pyramid pose 
5: Pigeon Pose
6: Double pigeon pose
7: Alternating knee pulls
8: Sidelyijg thoracic rotations

If you like this flow sign up for my #maelevate program with a whole community behind you @mawarriors 👇🏽 

www.MassyArias.com/elevate
#childofGod
_________________________________________

Día de recuperación  Día de recuperación. Es contrario a la intuición pensar que cuando estás adolorido después de un entrenamiento, lo que necesitas es movimiento para sentirte mejor. Aumentar el flujo sanguíneo y enviar sangre rica y oxigenada a esos músculos adoloridos acelerará la recuperación y disminuirá el dolor. Así que prueba este flow de movilidad / estiramiento los días en que se estés recuperando de entrenamientos duros. Empieza ligero y no forzes los movimientos. 

Al hacer este flow, mantén cada estiramiento durante 10 respiraciones profundas haciendo tres rondas de cada transición. 

1: Pinza de pie.
2: Plancha alta.
3: Pose guerrero 1.
4: Pose pirámide.
5: Pose de Paloma.
6: Pose doble paloma.
7: Estiramiento de glúteos con piernas alternadas.
8: Rotaciones torácicas.

Déjame saber qué tal te sientes. Preguntas? Házmelas en la sección de comentarios.

#hijadecristo

node.text:
Day 1 of my #MAELEVATE program @mawarriors. Here’s how we perform the workouts at home and how we will take at home training to another level.

Circuit training allows us to work smart and cut the time we spend working out. We are targeting the entire body with little to no rest in between.

Here’s one circuit of my Elevate 60 day at home program:

1: Goblet squat with iso hold : 8 reps 10s iso hold.
2: Plank circles: 8 circles per side.
3:Down dog to plank with 20s hold.

Benefits:

Isometric contractions make you strong and prevent injury. Before we move to more complex movements, we first set the foundation your body needs in order to perform functionally. Our first week we focus on getting your body strong, building muscular endurance and proprioception.

Try this circuit and follow along with me and join us @mawarriors . Will be posting full routine later today.

Where are my warriors at? Sign up 👇🏽 
www.MassyArias.com/elevate
___________________________________________

Los lunes son para ser conquistados. Aquí te dejo un circuito para que lo trates conmigo.

1: Sentadilla goblet con pausa isometrica: 8 repeticiones 10s iso. 
2: Circulos de cadera en plancha: 8 círculos por lado. 
3: Perro hacia abajo a plancha con pausa de 20 segundos isometrica. 

Beneficios: Las contracciones isométricas te fortalecen y previenen lesiones. Al
Entrenar en circuito podemos trabajar nuestro cuerpo completo con poco descanso y maximizar el tiempo de entrenamiento.

Trata este circuito y déjame saber que tal! 

Dale!

node.title: Elevate your training at home with circuit training #MAELEVATE LINK IN BIO!

node.text:
Because Monday’s are meant to be crushed. Lower body, core, aerobic workout. [save, share, and let’s get it]

Get ready to elevate. Unleashing the beast begins now...

The workout: perform all exercises of a circuit with little rest in between them. Drop questions on the comment section below.

Circuit 1: 5 sets
Dead squat deadlift 5x5sec iso hold
Ball slams 10
Modified plank with hip extension 6per side

Circuit 2: 4 sets 
Zertcher squat 6reps
Farmers walks 30 yards
Jump rope 1 minute

Circuit 3: 3 sets 
Low lunge scissors 10 per side
Single plank 20 secs per side
Serratus ball reach with hip extension 8 per side.

Today my #MAelevate drops. Enroll now and let me unleash your full potential. Sign up and let me be your coach

www.massyarias.com/elevate
#childofGod 
_________________________________________

Porque los lunes son para ser conquistados. Comenzamos la semana inspirándoles a dar lo mejor de ustedes. Este entrenamiento es avanzado. Piernas, abdominales, resistencia cardiovascular.

A esto le llamo cardio con pesas. 

El entrenamiento: hacer todas los ejercicios  de un circuito con poco descanso entre ellos. Descansa al terminar cada serie. 

Circuit 1: 5 series
Peso muerto: 5x5seg pausa isometrica.
Ball slams: 10 reps.
Plancha modificada con extensión de cadera: 6 reps por lado.

Circuit 2: 4 sets 
Sentadilla Zertcher : 6reps.
Caminata de granjero: 30 yardas.
Salto de cuerda: 1 minuto.

Circuit 3: 3 sets 
Zancada baja tijera: 10 por pierna.
Plancha con una sola pierna: 20 seg por lado.
Extension de cadera con bola de medicina: 8 por lado.

Dale!
#hijadecristo

node.text:
Oh baby, 🔥 💦 Let’s HIIT it at home full body [ share, tag a friend, save to crush it later]

How many of you are training from home? Never undertimate body weight training because it can be extremely effective, and challenging. Can’t wait for you to try it.

The workout: perform 4 sets of each superset. Each superset with little to no rest. 30s per movement. Rest 45-1minute between sets. 

1️⃣
Lateral bench jump burpee
Bench tricep extension with reverse crunch 
2️⃣
Reverse lunge with bench single leg step up jump.
Bench push up with knee drive.

3️⃣
Straddle bench squat jumps.
90 degree bench cross single arm crunch.

4️⃣
Bench single leg alternating bridge.
Elevated plank with alternating toe reach.

Tag me when you try it. Put your questions ⬇️ like this workout? Join my @mawarriors community with my #ma45day program.

www.Massyarias.com 
#mawarriors #childofGod
______________________________________________

Mi tribu, aquí les dejo hun entrenamiento de peso corporal asesino estilo HIIT cuerpo completo [compartelo, etiqueta a un amigo, guardalo para hacerlo  más tarde] 

¿Cuántos de ustedes están entrenando desde casa? 

El entrenamiento: realiza 3-4 series de cada superconjunto. Cada superconjunto con poco o ningún descanso. 30 segundos por movimiento. Descansa 45s-1 minuto entre súper conjunto. 

1️⃣
Salto lateral en banco con burpee
Extensión de tríceps con crunch invertido.
2️⃣
Zancada inversa con step up pliometrico en banco 
Pechada en banco con flexión de rodilla alternada.

3️⃣
Salto de sentadilla en banco.
Crunch abdominal alternado con pies en banco a 90 grados.

4️⃣
Puente en banco con rolas alternadas.
Plancha elevada con toque de dedo alternado.

Etiquétame cuando lo pruebes. Pon tus preguntas ⬇️ prepárense para una rutina increíble.

#hijadecristo

node.text:
A branch that doesn’t bend, BREAKS-Una rama que no se dobla, se Rompe. @mawarriors 

Tune in to your body after a long hard week and let’s go deep. Hold each pose/stretch 3 sets 45s-Minute.

Dale a ese cuerpo el descanso y el tango que necesita. Hoy nos vamos con movilidad profunda. 3 series de 45s a 1 minuto de aguante por cada estiramiento/pose.

For my circuit/yoga #maelevate program visit 👇🏽

www.MassyArias.com
#mawarriors #childofGod #hijadecristo

node.text:
Because Monday’s are meant to be crushed. The day you don’t feel like waking up to work on yourself, is the day you need it the most. This is how you build a mindset that will help you make this a lifestyle change.

Get up, get out, get moving. Let’s set the tone for the week. You got this. Picking up Muay Thai with the one of the greatest @greg_wootton.

When I picked up this discipline I did it to be able to defend myself in ang case I was in a compromised position. Not only to defend myself, but to defend my daughter. As a woman, do you feel like you can defend yourself if needed?

Exercise can go beyond aesthetics goals. Gain the confidence to take the first step- make yourself proud!

www.massyarias.com
#mawarriors #childofgod ————————————————————— Porque los Lunes están hechos para ser conquistados. El día que no tengas las  ganas de levantarse para trabajar en ti mismo, es el día en que más lo necesitas. Así es como creas la mentalidad que te ayudará a hacer  un cambio de estilo de vida. Levántate, esfuérzate , muévete. Vamos a darle el tono a la semana. 

Como mujer, sientes que si estás en una situación comprometedora puedes defenderte? Tome esta disciplina como precaución y para ganar confianza en mi misma-poder defenderme y también a mi hija. 

El wjercicio va más allá de lo estético. Tienes que tomar el primer paso, hoy dale el tono de confianza a ti mismo/a para conquistar la semana.

Dale!

#hijadecristo

Grab your suspension trainer. Let’s finish the week strong with Full body core 🔥 🍑 💦 [tag a friend to challenge, save for later, let’s get it] @mawarriors.

The workout: perform each movement of each  circuit with little to no rest in between. Perform 3-4 sets. Rest when circuit is completed 1-2mins between sets. Go double leg on the movements that may be too advanced for you.

Circuit 1:
•Single leg reverse lunge to pistol squat 8 reps.
•Trx single leg row 6 reps each.
•Trx leaning alternating skips 20s
Circuit 2:
 
•Trx squat with bicep curl 8 reps
•Trx boat crunches 8 reps.
•Trx Leg abductions with knee drive  8 reps

Circuit 3
 • Trx squat jumps 20s
•Trx tricep extensions 8 reps
 • Trx seated alternating knee drives 6 per side 

I want to see you guys move it. Tag me if you crush it.  Song @santigold #disparateyouth

🛑Join my  community and let me help you reach your goals and change your lifestyle with my at home MA programs 👇🏽 

www.Massyarias.com
#childofGod #maelevate
___________________________________________

Rutina épica de cuerpo completo. Prepárense que este esta increíble [salvalo y menciona a un amigo que quieras retar. Los ejercicios con una sola pierna pueden ser modificados por doble pierna.

Completa 3-4 series de cada circuito por la repeticiones dadas. Realiza cada movimiento de cada circuito con poco o ningún descanso entre movimientos. Descansa después de completar cada set del circuito.

Circuito 1:
 • Zancada reversa con sentadilla pistol 8 reps.
•Trx remo con una sola pierna 6 reps each.
• Trx rodillas alternadas 30s

Circuito 2:
 
•Trx Sentadilla con flexión de biceps 8 reps
• Crunch a pose note con Trx 8 reps.
• 8 reps
 • Abducciones de piernas con flexión de rodilla en Trx 8 reps.

Circuito 3

•Salto de Sentadilla con trx 20s
•Extensión de tríceps con suspensión trx 8 repsRodillas alternadas con adducion de brazos 6 reps por lado. 

Prepárate a sudar. Mencióname si lo tratas! Dale, a quien retas a usar sus cuerpos como máquinas?

#hijadecristo

node.text:
Who is training at the gym vs at home? Get ready to feel the 🔥 at home @mawarriors [save, share, let’s crush it] this is a glute, lower body, and core focused routine from my at home glute program.

The workout: 9 glute/core/lower body movements broken down in three circuits. Perform each movement of each circuit with little to no rest in between. 3-4 rounds.
Whether  you’re doing this body weight or with resistance, this is how we train functionally and for results.

Bulgarian split squats : 3 setsx8 reps with 10s hold at bottom. Slow tempo.
Bicycle crunch feet at 90: 3x8
Band lateral walks: 3x8

Forward to back lunge: 3x10
Single leg concentric squats: 3x8reps
Single leg Bucks: 3x10

Single leg counterbalance squat: 3x8 (stack up more pillows if lacking range of motion. Use a 5-10 dumbbell to assist if lacking strength).
Warrior 3 pose with pulses: 3x30s
Supine pelvic rotations: 3x 8 reps.

Happy Wednesday tribe , let me know how you liked this workout. Program available on my website, join the tribe 👇🏽 

www.massyarias.com
#childofGod #mawarriors 

_____________________________________________________

Como se los prometí. Aquí les dejo un entrenamiento de piernas, glúteos, y abdominales desde casa. El peso es relativo a tu nivel de fuerza. Puedes hacerlo con tu peso corporal o añadir mancuernas.

El entrenamiento: realizarás cada movimiento de cada circuito con poco o ningún descanso entre ellos.

Sentadilla búlgara: 3 series x 8 repeticiones con aguante isometrico de 10s. 
Crunch bicicleta con piernas 90 grados: 3x8
Caminata lateral con banda: 3x8

Zancada doble : 3x10
Sentadilla concéntrica con una sola pierna: 3x8reps
Bucks con una sola pierna: 3x10

Sentadilla contrapeso: 3x8
Pulsadas de extensión de cadera en posición warrior 3: 3x30segundos
Rotaciones pélvicas: 3x 8 

Déjame saber qué tal te fue en este entrenamiento. Preguntas? 👇🏽 

#hijdecristo

node.text:
Monday’s are meant to be ________?  Los Lunes son para ser _______? 

This week and every week we set the tone. We set the tone to succeed.
To get back up when we fall and do it with confidence.
To learn from the falls and turn those into action items.

“You are the artist of your own life, don’t give the paintbrush to anyone else”.

Let’s get to work tribe. Announcing something very exciting this week. Get excited your coach is so ready to take your mindset to a whole new level.

@mawarriors 

www.massyarias.com
#childofGod #maelevate
_________________________________________

 Esta semana y todas las semanas le damos el tono. Marcamos el tono para triunfar. Para volver a levantarnos cuando caemos y hacerlo con confianza. Para aprender de los fallos y convertirlos en elementos de acción. “Eres el artista de tu propia vida, no le des el pincel a nadie más”. 

Vamos a trabajar mi tribu !

node.text: Today we celebrate love. Look how big she’s gotten guys. My angel || Hoy celebramos el amor. Miren que grandota está la indi mi tribu.

node.text:
Oh baby 🔥💦 Leg day for function, strength, and gains [save, share, let’s get it @mawarriors || Una rutina funcional para piernas [salvalo y compártelo. 

The workout: perform every movement  of each circuit back to back with little rest in between. Complete 3-4 sets of a circuit before moving to the next. 

El entrenamiento: completarás cada movimiento de cada circuito con poco descanso entre ellos. Harás 3-4
sets  de cada circuito.

Circuit 1️⃣
. Single arm rack squat / Sentadilla rack con un solo brazo 6 reps per side/ por lado.
. Kb Linear lunge / Zancada linear con pesa rusa  6 reps por lado 
• 1/4 Turkish get up 6 reps per side/por lado.

Circuit 2️⃣
•Reverse lunge to step up/ Zancada hacia atrás con step up 6 reps per side/por lado.
•Kb pick ups / Recojidas de pesa rusa / 6 per side/ por lado .
•Kb windmill / Windmill con pesa rusa 6reps per side/ por lado

Circuit 3️⃣
•Single leg Kb / Sentadilla con una sola pierna  6 reps.
•Single leg bridge/ Hip thrust con una sola pierna  6 reps per side/por lado.
•single arm kb Alternating dead bug /  extensión de pesa rusa con deadbug alternado 6 reps per side/por lado.
 
Have fun with this one. If you liked this workout then you’re going to love my new #MA60day program. 👇🏽 
www.massyarias.com/programs
#childofGod #hijadecristo #mawarriors

node.text:
[read below] How can you control your hunger and your cravings? Balancing your meals is key when it comes to controlling hunger. 

•Choose carbs with a high fiber profile. Fiber slows down digestion, which allows you to feel fuller, longer. •Add a lean protein source; it will help you feel satisfied for longer by affecting the hormones which control hunger and how fast food empties from our stomachs. Your body also uses the most calories to digest this macronutrient. 
•Healthy fats. I like to keep my 3 main meals ( breakfast, lunch, and dinner) with moderate fat so I can enjoy snacks that are a little higher in fat. Where’s the healthy fat here? The olive oil I used to cook these items.

•Let’s not forget about the importance of micronutrients (veggies and fruits). They provide the body with the nutrients that will keep your body healthy.

One of my snacks contains a fruit which I have early during the day. An apple with a serving of almond butter is a great example. 

I stay energized, control hunger, and have better body composition.

www.massyarias.com
#childofGod 
_________________________________________________

¿Cómo puedes controlar tu hambre y tus antojos? Come para controlar tu apetito. 

•Elige carbohidratos altos en fibra. La fibra retarda la digestión, lo que le permite sentirse más lleno, por más tiempo. 
• Añade una fuente de proteína magra. Te ayudará a sentirse satisfecho por más tiempo al afectar las hormonas que controlan el hambre. Tu cuerpo también utiliza la mayoría de las calorías para dijerir este macronutrients. 

•Grasas saludables. Me gusta mantener mis 3 comidas principales (desayuno, almuerzo y cena) con grasas moderadas y balancear mis meriendas con un poco más de grasas. 

¿Dónde está la grasa saludable aquí? En el aceite de oliva que cociné la comida.

• No olvidemos los micronutrientes. Es clave que nos enfoquemos en la importancia de las vitaminas y minerales que las frutas y verduras proporcionan para la salud. Una de mis 2 meriendas contiene una fruta durante el día. 1 manzana verde y 1 porción de mantequilla de mani es un gran ejemplo. 

Me mantengo con energía, controlo el hambre y mejoro mi composición corporal.

node.text:
Wrist pain? This video is long overdue. Do you experience wrist pain when exercising? [save it, share it, and read below]

Here ar some tips on stretches and exercises you can do to not strain your wrists while exercising.

Tip 1: keep your resists flexible in all planes of motion. Without an adequate range of motion in our wrist we end up compressing into a joint that isn’t ready to take on that pressure passively or actively. 

How many reps/weight? Well, listen to your body and be gentle. The more you perform these and be progressive with the work (as in- every day before a workout) the less you have to worry about reps, and focus on how you feel. Take 5 mins and make these a habit.

1️⃣ Warm up flexibility work: 

1:Extended arms wrist flexión and extension.
2:Extended arms wrist rotations.
3:All 4’s rotation/flexion/extension variations.

2️⃣ Strong wrists are more stable during weight-bearing exercises. Strengthening your wrists and forearms (as the forearms control the wrists) is also key not only to be able to hold heavier weight more securely, but to bear the load of your own body weight or push/pull weight. 

1: Farmers walks (walk 50-100 feet. Use progressive weight). These are great to add to your workout prescriptions. 
2: Dumbbell  flexión and extension.
3: Dumbell  pronation and supination.

If you are injured, recovering from injury, and or are experiencing extreme inflammation and pain consult a PT. These tips are for healthy individuals who don’t require medical help. 

Let me know how these do for you. 

Join my tribe pointing down 👇🏽 

www.massyarias.com
#mawarriors #childofGod

¿Dolor de muñeca? ¿Sientes dolor de muñeca al hacer ejercicio? [guárdalo, compártelo y lee a continuación] 

Aquí hay algunos consejos sobre estiramientos y ejercicios que puedes hacer para no tensar las muñecas mientras haces ejercicio. 

Consejo 1: menten tus muñecas flexibles en todos los planos de movimiento. Sin un rango de movimiento adecuado en nuestra muñeca, terminamos comprimiéndonos en una articulación que no está lista para asumir esa presión de forma pasiva o activa. 

Continuación en los comentarios.
